cs.IR, cs.HC, cs.CL, cs.CY, cs.CR

This paper is about studying the performance of ordinary users while carrying out search tasks on commercial Web search engines. The study involves assessing the difficulty, time effort, query effort, and task outcome of search tasks, and how their judging performance relates to task complexity. This topic falls under the sub-category of Information Retrieval (cs.IR) as it deals with search engines and search tasks. It also involves Human-Computer Interaction (cs.HC) as it studies the performance of ordinary users while interacting with search engines. Additionally, it involves Computational Linguistics (cs.CL) as it deals with the language used in search queries. Cybersecurity (cs.CY) and Cryptography and Security (cs.CR) are less likely sub-categories as they are not directly related to the topic of the paper.
